<br>
More times than not, it'll follow a simple pattern. example is using consecutive rolls, over a short period of time. /rand 100<br>
<br>
Some number 34-66....\<br>
Some number 34-66.....|- some number of these<br>
Some number 34-66..../<br>
Some number 1-33....1-3 of these<br>
Some number 67-100....1-2 of these, then back to the mid numbers.<br>
<br>
If it's a busy area, and all the scammers...err...casino operators have a large number of marks, and the /randoms are really flowing; if you jam your /random in right after some other smuck gets a 20, you're rather likely to get a 67 or better.  If you don't you'll likely get a 15 to go along with him, and someone else who's paying attention will get the 67+ _right_ after.<br>
<br>
Of course, the above comes into play alot more on the /random's you get on the misc crap that drops while exping....<br>
